Today, most of us use our mobile phones to access Microsoft Teams, Outlook, SharePoint, or company emails.
Some of us use corporate laptops, some use personal devices under BYOD.

Now the question is —
How does the organization ensure that corporate data is secure on all these devices?”

Pause.

“This is where Microsoft Intune comes in.”

🔹 What It Is

“Microsoft Intune is a cloud-based Unified Endpoint Management solution.

Under Intune, we have two major capabilities:

• MDM – Mobile Device Management
• MAM – Mobile Application Management

MDM manages the entire device.
MAM manages only the corporate applications and data.”

🔹 Simple Difference (Say This Clearly)

“If the device is company-owned and fully enrolled — Intune uses MDM to control the whole device.

If it’s a personal device — Intune can use MAM to protect only corporate apps like Outlook and Teams, without touching personal data.”

That’s the key difference.

🔹 What It Protects

“Intune protects:

• Multiple platforms — iOS, Android, Windows, macOS
• Corporate data inside apps and devices
• Identity and access by allowing only compliant devices to access company resources

So even if a device is lost, stolen, or jailbroken, access can be blocked immediately.”

🔹 Key Capabilities

“Some important capabilities include:

• Zero-touch device enrollment using Windows Autopilot or Apple Business Manager
• Compliance policies — enforcing PIN, encryption, OS version
• Remote actions — lock, reset, or selective wipe
• App protection policies — preventing copy-paste of company data into personal apps

So IT gets control, but user privacy is still maintained.”

🔹 Organizational Value

“This helps organizations:

• Support secure BYOD
• Reduce IT overhead with centralized cloud management
• Enforce security automatically using Conditional Access

So instead of trusting devices blindly, access is granted only if the device is secure and compliant.”

🔹 Strong Closing Line

“In simple terms,
Microsoft Intune ensures that no matter where employees work from — corporate data stays protected, devices stay compliant, and access remains controlled.”
